entries.title: Second batch of classified Biden documents discovered during extensive search
entries.description: Aides to Joe Biden have found a second batch of documents, some of which may be classified, at a new location that Biden was known to use, ABC News has learned

entries.title: Musician Jeff Beck dies suddenly at 78
entries.description: Musician Jeff Beck has died suddenly after contracting bacterial meningitis, according to his family.

entries.title: Alleged gun smugglers indicted in New York City under new federal law
entries.description: Four men were arrested Wednesday in a gun trafficking conspiracy case that federal prosecutors said was the first of its kind under a new federal law.

entries.title: First lady Jill Biden has cancerous lesion removed from near her right eye
entries.description: Dr. Kevin O'Connor said "all cancerous tissue was successfully removed" during the procedure.

entries.title: Killer whale dies after beaching itself on Florida coast
entries.description: A 21-foot killer whale has died after beaching itself on the Atlantic coast in central Florida

entries.title: Wisconsin man's retrial begins in wife's antifreeze death
entries.description: The trial comes nearly two years after a judge vacated his previous conviction.

entries.title: Supermodel Tatjana Patitz dies at age 56
entries.description: Famed German supermodel Tatjana Patitz died on Jan. 11 in Santa Barbara, California.

entries.title: Biden leaves questions unanswered on classified documents, as GOP pounces
entries.description: President Joe Biden on Wednesday faced a growing political headache after classified documents were found in his former office in Washington.

entries.title: FDA adds sesame to major food allergen list
entries.description: Sesame allergen labeling on food packages is required as of January 1, 2023, according to the FDA.

entries.title: Top Russian military officer put in charge of Ukraine action
entries.description: Russia’s top military officer has been put in charge of troops fighting in Ukraine on Wednesday

entries.title: US official warns of risks posed by heavy electric vehicles
entries.description: The head of the National Transportation Safety Board is expressing concern about the safety risks that heavy electric vehicles pose if they collide with lighter vehicles

entries.title: Officers plead not guilty in Randy Cox case, the man paralyzed in police custody
entries.description: The five New Haven, Connecticut, police officers charged in the case of Randy Cox, a Black man who was paralyzed while being transported in custody, pleaded not guilty.

entries.title: Miami-Dade wins right to strip FTX name off Heat arena
entries.description: The naming rights deal between FTX and Miami-Dade County has been terminated by a federal bankruptcy court

entries.title: Brazil authorities brace for possible repeat of uprising
entries.description: Brazil’s capital is bracing for the possibility of more violent demonstrations by people seeking to overturn the presidential election

entries.title: WATCH:  Puppy bus filled with furry riders
entries.description: Mo Mountain Mutts in Skagway, Alaska, assigns seats to about 40 pups based on personality and age for meetups.

entries.title: Alleged 'boogaloo' member denies threatening law enforcement
entries.description: An Ohio man who federal officials say is a member of the far-right anti-government group the boogaloo boys has pleaded not guilty to charges that he threatened law enforcement and unlawfully possessed a machine gun

entries.title: NY Republicans call on Rep. George Santos to resign over his 'deceit'
entries.description: New York Republicans on Wednesday called on George Santos to resign following revelations that he fabricated or embellished much of his background

entries.title: Car insurance rates to rise 8.4% in 2023: Report
entries.description: The average cost of full coverage car insurance will be $1,780 a year, report finds.

entries.title: Poland to send Leopard tanks to Ukraine, if others do, too
entries.description: Polish President Andrzej Duda says that the European Union nation has decided to send a company of Leopard tanks to help neighboring Ukraine in the war with invading Russia

entries.title: Iran sentences ex-official to death over alleged UK spying
entries.description: An Iranian state-linked news agency says a former senior defense official has been sentenced to death after being convicted of spying for Britain

entries.title: Supreme Court lets New York enforce gun law during lawsuit
entries.description: The Supreme Court is allowing New York to continue to enforce for now a sweeping new law banning guns from “sensitive places” such as schools, playgrounds and Times Square and increasing training requirements

entries.title: Numbers of refugees, asylum-seekers increase in Germany
entries.description: More than 244,000 people have applied for asylum in Germany last year and more than 1 million Ukrainian refugees who have come to the country looking for shelter from Russia’s war

entries.title: WATCH:  Golfers flee as huge wave hits Pebble Beach golf course
entries.description: A huge wave at a golf course along California’s coast sent golfers running inland and swamped their golf carts.

entries.title: WATCH:  Russian rocket hits fireworks warehouse in Kharkiv
entries.description: Russian rockets hit Kharkiv, Ukraine, setting a fireworks warehouse ablaze, according to local officials.

entries.title: WATCH:  Elderly man rescued from vehicle amid California flood
entries.description: An elderly man was rescued after floodwaters submerged his vehicle in Santa Barbara, California.

entries.title: Oil price cap takes small slice of Russia war chest: Report
entries.description: Russia's still making plenty of money from oil sales despite a price cap imposed by the Group of Seven major democracies

entries.title: Wall Street futures inch up ahead of US inflation report
entries.description: Wall Street pointed modestly higher before the bell as markets try to extend what’s been a strong start to the year after a mostly dreadful 2022

entries.title: UK, Japan sign defense deal amid rising concern about China
entries.description: The leaders of Britain and Japan are signing a defense agreement that could see troops deployed to each others’ countries

entries.title: China renews threat against Taiwan as island holds drills
entries.description: China has renewed its threat to attack Taiwan, warning foreign politicians who interact with the self-governing island that they are “playing with fire."

entries.title: China preparing to expand airline service to United States
entries.description: Chinese state TV says Beijing is preparing to allow airlines to fly more routes between China and the United States following the end of anti-virus travel restrictions

entries.title: First lady set to have skin lesion removed near her right eye
entries.description: First lady Dr. Jill Biden will undergo an outpatient procedure on Wednesday to remove a small lesion found above her right eye.

entries.title: Computer failure at FAA could impact flights nationwide
entries.description: A computer failure at the FAA has the potential to impact flights nationwide, including a possible nationwide grounding, ABC News has learned.

entries.title: Illinois becomes latest US state to ban assault weapons
entries.description: For Illinois, the ban came six months after a gunman wielding a semiautomatic rifle shot and killed seven people at a 4th of July parade in a Chicago suburb.

entries.title: Man charged after multiple dogs found dead in dumpster
entries.description: A man has been arrested after multiple dogs were found dead in a dumpster during a period of several weeks at the end of last year.

entries.title: Paris train station attack leaves multiple people injured
entries.description: A man has left multiple people injured following an attack at the Gare Du Nord station in Paris early Wednesday morning, authorities say.

entries.title: Amtrak Auto Train that was stuck after freight derailment is moving again
entries.description: An Amtrak Auto Train detoured off its normal route due to the derailment of a CSX freight Monday night and was stuck while waiting for a new crew to arrive.

entries.title: WATCH:  Giant boulders rain down on highway as monster storm hits California
entries.description: Highway patrol officers in central California blocked traffic on State Route 168 after massive boulders rained down on the highway as stormy weather slammed the region.

entries.title: EXPLAINER: How much will the rain help California's drought?
entries.description: The series of storms that have struck California have poured water on a state mired in a years-long drought

entries.title: Cardinal Pell, whose convictions were overturned, dies at 81
entries.description: Cardinal George Pell, a onetime financial adviser to Pope Francis who had sex abuse convictions overturned, has died

entries.title: House Oversight Committee investigating classified documents found at Biden's office
entries.description: The House Oversight Committee, led by Republican Rep. James Comer, is investigating Joe Biden's handling of classified records

entries.title: Commercial fishermen offered 'bounty' to clean up ocean
entries.description: Commercial fishermen have been offered a bounty to collect derelict fishing gear, often the culprit of the death of marine animals, and bring the debris back to shore.
